&lt;p&gt;Can you provide an example or test that fails based on the sources in Git master? Include your configuration file as well please.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Gary&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15444157" author="garydgregory" created="Sun, 28 Aug 2016 21:31:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Might have found something with &lt;tt&gt;org.apache.logging.log4j.core.appender.CsvJsonParameterLayoutFileAppenderTest&lt;/tt&gt;...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15444161" author="garydgregory" created="Sun, 28 Aug 2016 21:34:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think the problem is that a 0x00 is written for the header and footer. If you add &quot;&quot; for header and footer, this is not a problem... something needs tweaking...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15445065" author="sumit23" created="Mon, 29 Aug 2016 07:16:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Just to clarify Gary, the problem appears with a specific type of data, (JSON or starting with braces as mentioned). NUL character does not appear with normal strings.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
